This paper focuses on improving the visual understanding capacity of computers by recognizing human sign language more efficiently through facial expression recognition. This involves the use of computer vision techniques and deep neural networks, which are commonly associated with the computer vision (cs.CV) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the use of a customized architecture for the deep neural network, which falls under the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper aims to improve communication for the deaf community, which falls under the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the paper deals with recognizing emotions, which is a topic commonly associated with multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
